We are excited to announce that The Next Era Program is back for year 2!
@vans and Columbus, Ohio-based non-profit organization, Look Ma' No Hands (LMNH), connect to create 'The Next Era'; a one-of-a-kind program designed to expose 20 High School-age youth to careers within the fashion industry. This FREE, 6-month fully comprehensive program will be held twice per week beginning January 17th, 2023, through June 28th, 2022, and consists of a collaborative curriculum taught by Vans staff, LMNH staff, and special guest educators from their respective professional backgrounds. Each student will be provided with an iPad that they will keep to complete the work, as well as access to industry leading software.
 
Last year we were able to take 20 students from across Central Ohio to create a community that fills the void in the support that youth need take more pride in their lives. Giving them to chance to recognize that opportunities are possible and present. 
 
The application process requires that each student interested in joining the program 1.) submits an application, 2.) writes a personal statement, and 3.) gets a letter of recommendation. The complete application can be found on https://WWW.LMNH.org/.
Submissions are due January 3rd 2023! If you have any questions, please email Jalynn@lmnh.org

Some of our favorite people on the planet are educators, teachers, administrators, and counselors; the unsung heroes who have helped raise and mold us all. At Sole Classics, we are extremely proud to announce our first of two annual Teacher Appreciation Months. 

During the month of January a portion of our sales will go right into the pockets of four deserving Central Ohio educators. No gimmicks, no gift cards, no toys for their students. A check folded up and put into an envelope, then slid into their pocket. 

From December 26th until December 31st at 11:59PM EST you can nominate an educator that has left a lifetime impression on you by clicking the link in our bio. We will review the submissions and select four beaming lights in our community to participate. When you shop with us during the month of January just mention “TEACHER” (or enter it at checkout online) and you’ll receive a discount along with a percentage of the sale going into the pot to be split evenly between the four teachers to use to buy a flight away from your snotty son, put a down payment on a car, pay their coffee tab for the year, or just to hold up to their ear on IG. 

Why are we doing this? Well, we aren’t even sure if January is the official Teacher’s Appreciation Month, but our team had an idea and we can do whatever we want. Also, because we know that our educators deserve more and we just want to do our part, no matter how big or small it is. 

Stay tuned for more details and announcements, but click the link in our bio and nominate your favorite Central Ohio teacher, principal, counselor, administrator, or educator today. Participants will be announced on January 5th.
